rulebank_rules.text: Verify every visual claim against image; never infer or invent unobserved elements.
Quantify visible elements precisely (e.g., exact people count) before assigning scores.
Verify every claimed detail (e.g., markings) against image before including in rationale.
Assess inherent structural risks like steepness, not only visible damage or maintenance.
Never assign unconfirmed species names; describe visuals and quote labels exactly.
Precisely verify small object identities against image to eliminate hallucinations.
